  "market_context": "London session swept a prior high, formed a reversal with CISD (close below up-close candles), then NY session opened at 8:30 with an opposing upward manipulation move before price retested the bearish order block and continued lower.",
  "key_observation": "Price formed a London reversal via CISD, NY 8:30 manipulated up (opposing to bias), creating a bearish order block that was retested and triggered a 2R continuation lower.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst identified London session reaching a high with a series of up-close candles, then observed a close below them—confirming a Change in State of Delivery (CISD) and London reversal.",
    "Step 2: As NY session approached, analyst noted the 8:30 economic open moved higher (opposing the bearish bias), interpreting it as a manipulation move to induce longs before continuing lower.",
    "Step 3: Analyst identified the bearish order block formed by the candle closing below the up-close series; price retested this OB during NY session and entered short with stop above the 8:30 manipulation high.",
    "Step 4: Trade targeted 2R, achieved near 10:00 AM, coinciding with a key time level (4H open structure) and continuation lower."
  ],
  "outcome": "2R profit achieved; price made a new low around 10:00 AM EST.",
  "lessons": "A London reversal confirmed by CISD sets the bias; NY 8:30 opposing manipulation often creates high-probability bearish OB entries. Always align with HTF structure and target 2R minimum.",
